"Correctional officer" means an employee of the Department working in a State correctional facility who serves in the classification of correctional officer I, II, sergeant, lieutenant, captain, or major, and includes:
a correctional dietary officer;
a correctional maintenance officer;
a correctional laundry officer;
a correctional recreation officer; and
a correctional supply officer.

"Misconduct" means:
engaging in intentional behavior, without justification, that injures another person, causes damage to property, or threatens the safety of the workplace;
engaging in unjustifiably offensive conduct toward fellow employees, inmates, or the public;
using excessive force in the treatment or care of an inmate;
possessing or trafficking in contraband at a Department facility;
being on duty while under the influence of alcohol or a controlled dangerous substance, or while engaged in the illegal use of a prescription drug;
engaging in a social, personal, intimate, or sexual relationship with an inmate;
stealing State property with a value of $300 or less;
engaging in conduct involving dishonesty, fraud, deceit, misrepresentation, or illegality;
willfully making a false official statement or report;
violating a lawful order or failing to obey a lawful order given by a superior;
engaging in any of the actions that are cause for automatic termination of employment under § 11-105 of the State Personnel and Pensions Article; or
committing any violation of the Department's Standards of Conduct.
